message.content:
cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.AR, cs.PL, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper presents a new approach to prevent return address manipulation attacks using message authentication codes.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also likely as the paper discusses the implementation of the approach on the ARMv8.3-A architecture.
- cs.AR (Architecture) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of hardware-assisted shadow stacks and the implementation on a specific architecture.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper discusses the control-flow integrity of a program and the manipulation of function return addresses.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper presents a new approach to secure the call stack of a system.
